<module>
    <h>sibh</h>
    <p><g>sibh</g>
        <en>you</en> is the second person plural <a href="?xx=nouns/personal_pronouns">personal
            pronoun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <!--<p><g>sibh</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>-->
            <p>Examples with the predicative verb <g href="?gd=bi">bi</g>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha sibh trang ag obair anns an achadh agus tha sibh sgìth.</gd>
                        <tr>You are busy working in the field and you are tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha sibh aig an teine.</gd>
                        <tr>You are at the fire.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [226]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil sibh ag obair? Tha.</gd>
                        <tr>Are you working? Yes, I am.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 13</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil sibh fliuch? Chan eil.</gd>
                        <tr>Are you wet? No, I’m not.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Ciamar a tha sibh? Tha mi gu math, tapadh leibh.</gd>
                        <tr>How are you? I am well, thank you.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh sibh anns an achadh an diugh? Cha robh.</gd>
                        <tr>Were you in the field today? No, I wasn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 17</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>




</module>
